<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 5: ROCKER ARM ASSEMBLY, CAMSHAFT
        ASSEMBLY, TAPPETS AND PUSH RODS - CAMSHAFT BUSHING INSPECTION
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>CAMSHAFT BUSHING INSPECTION</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="2">
            <title>INSPECTION</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect the four (4) camshaft bushings for wear and proper running clearance as
                    follows:
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Using a micrometer, measure camshaft bushing journal diameter at two (2) locations,
                        90&#176; apart and record readings.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Using a telescoping gauge (
                        <emph type="bold">OEM1022</emph>) and micrometer, measure the camshaft bushing I.D. with bushing
                        installed in the crankcase. Record the readings.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="ef1600524" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg5327" filename="../figeg5/eg5327.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 5.24 Installing Camgear Onto Camshaft</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef1600525" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg5328" filename="../figeg5/eg5328.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 5.25 Check Camshaft End Play</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Subtract the readings obtained in steps 1a and b, to determine running clearance.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">If maximum allowable running clearance is exceeded (see
                        <hotlnk xrefid="hl1600501">"SPECIFICATIONS"</hotlnk>), replace the camshaft bushings using the
                        camshaft bushing remover and installer (
                        <emph type="bold">ZTSE2893C</emph>).
                    </para>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>WHEN SERVICING THE CAMSHAFT BUSHINGS, THE CRANKSHAFT AND MAIN BEARING MUST BE REMOVED
                                FROM THE CRANKCASE TO AVOID DEBRIS CONTAMINATION.
                            </para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                </step2>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
